rComments: This prof is knowledgeable in reinforced concrete design. He is a dry lecturer and some of his examples/assignment solutions can have mistakes. His exams were fair, but you have to study well for them. Assignments are simple since they are similar to the examples seen in class. A lab report is assigned, I suggest starting early as it is quite long.

Somewhat dry lecturer but knows his material very well. His midterm was extremely hard, but he was willing to transfer the weight to the final. His exams are open everything, you can even bring a laptop. So if you don't know it, you're screwed.

This course is not fair! If you want take this course you must have previous assignements and exams otherwise you have no chance to get a good average! He uses the same assignments and exams, which I didin't know back then infortunately. Most students have the documents so no one complaints for this unethical practice! Good luck if you don't!
Amazing professor by all means however ... ONE COMMENT VERY HARSH ON GRADING!!!!! other than that he is absolutely amazing.

Amazing prof by all means. He is extremely patient with student and teaching them and helping them he is willing to meet you at anytime to help you.  Helpful through exams and extremely kind guy and very easy exams exactly as you expect them. !!!
Prof has alot of knowledge and expertise in earthquake engineering, not the most entertaining professors but is easy to understand and marks fairly.
Dr. Murat is very kind and helpful professor at the civil engineering department.
